25. You want to increase the memory limit of a pod. How do you modify the pod's resource limits?

EXPLAIN IN THIS ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
To modify the resource limits (CPU/memory) for a pod, you need to update the resource requests and limits in the podâ€™s YAML definition.

Example modification:

apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: my-pod
spec:
  containers:
  - name: my-container
    image: nginx
   resources:
     requests:
       memory: "64Mi"
       cpu: "250m"
     limits:
       memory: "128Mi"
       cpu: "500m"

Apply the updated YAML:
ğŸ‘‰ kubectl apply -f pod.yaml
To ensure the pod is restarted with the new limits, you can delete the pod or trigger a deployment update.
